THE RISK:
{
 "id": "buyer-mix-fabricated-odm-leakage",
 "title": "The 0.40 'large operators buy direct' share is one misread order-book stat — and the corpus says the real large-operator volume flows through ODM white-label the entrant can't intercept",
 "narrative": "The venture's stated go-to-market is 'large operators first', and the model rewards that with a 0.40 customer-type slice. But the only attached evidence for 0.40 is a company-level statistic (one supplier's DC orders = 30% of its book) that says nothing about buyer channels, and cust.oem/distributor carry zero evidence. Meanwhile the same digest documents the actual structure: hyperscale and large-colo procurement increasingly runs through Taiwanese ODM/white-label programs (Digipower, GETEKnet) and master distributors — spend that is nominally 'large operator' but contractually locked into OEM design-win cycles a pre-launch EU brand cannot enter in Year 1. The largest customer node isn't just uncertain; it is partly not a channel this entrant can address at all.",
 "category": "model-structure",
 "targetNodes": [
  "cust.operator-large",
  "cust.oem"
 ],
 "mechanism": [
  {
   "step": "trigger",
   "text": "cust.operator-large's 0.40 rests on a single order-mix datapoint (DC = 30% of one supplier's orders) misused as a market channel split; no source publishes any numeric buyer-channel breakdown",
   "refs": [
    "digest:cust-mix#c0",
    "ledger:cust.operator-large"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "propagation",
   "text": "Documented ODM/white-label supply (Digipower serving 'global OEM partners and infrastructure operators', GETEKnet as explicit OEM rack-PDU supplier, distributors offering private-label) means a material fraction of large-operator PDU volume is procured as white-label design wins with multi-year qualification cycles, not open branded tenders",
   "refs": [
    "digest:cust-mix#c11",
    "digest:cust-mix#c12",
    "digest:cust-mix#c13",
    "digest:cust-mix#c8"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "model-impact",
   "text": "The direct-branded large-operator slice shrinks (0.40→~0.27) while the OEM/integrator slice grows — but grows in a channel where a pre-launch entrant competes on ODM economics and 18–24 month qualification, so the venture's declared primary channel overstates its Year-1 reachable spend",
   "refs": [
    "ledger:cust.operator-large",
    "ledger:cust.oem",
    "profile:Who is the primary buyer you'll sell through first?"
   ]
  }
 ],
 "whyMissable": "The four buyer-mix numbers sum neatly to 1.00 and mirror the capacity mix, so the axis looks internally consistent; and 'sell to large operators' matches the segment story (hyperscale+colo = 62%). Nothing on the surface reveals that the largest cell was extrapolated from a statistic about a different question, or that its volume is contractually routed through a channel with different economics.",
 "expectedObviousness": "medium",
 "falsifier": "Three structured CE operator/distributor interviews (the node's own promotion path) confirming that ≥35% of CE rack-PDU spend is direct operator purchase of branded units on open tender.",
 "likelihood": {
  "value": 0.42,
  "rationale": "The evidentiary hole is documented in the digest (zero attached evidence for three of four nodes, one misused stat for the fourth), and ODM white-label supply is qualitatively confirmed by multiple vendors; only the magnitude of the shift is uncertain [evidence revision: The qualitative existence of ODM/white-label and private-label large-operator supply channels is well corroborated (GETEKnet, Digipower, PDU sourcing trend piece), strengthening the structural mechanism. But no source supplies any numeric channel split to validate the specific 0.40→0.27 magnitude claim, and the McKinsey source documents a countervailing trend of large B2B buyers moving toward direct OEM engagement — mildly undercutting the assumption that large-operator spend is contractually unreachable. Net effect is roughly neutral, so likelihood is held near the prior with a slight downward nudge for the unresolved magnitude and the countervailing direct-engagement signal.]",
  "basis": "evidence",
  "revisedFrom": 0.45
 },
 "perturbation": [
  {
   "nodeId": "cust.operator-large",
   "op": "set",
   "value": 0.27,
   "note": "Direct branded large-operator spend rewritten down; part of the former 0.40 is ODM-locked"
  },
  {
   "nodeId": "cust.oem",
   "op": "set",
   "value": 0.3,
   "note": "Mix shift: volume reappears in the OEM/ODM channel — deliberately nets -5pp because some white-label volume is unaddressable to a CE brand entrant at any price"
  }
 ],
 "indicators": [
  {
   "signal": "PDU specification language in large CE operator RFQs — 'ODM/white-label per our spec' vs open branded procurement",
   "where": "Hyperscaler supplier-registration portals and Frankfurt/Amsterdam colocation fit-out RFQ packages",
   "threshold": "≥2 of first 5 target accounts procuring PDUs exclusively via ODM programs or rack-integrator bundles",
   "updates": "increases"
  },
  {
   "signal": "Channel-mix commentary from incumbents — direct vs partner revenue split in EMEA",
   "where": "Vertiv EMEA partner-program materials and quarterly earnings channel commentary; Schneider partner announcements",
   "threshold": "Incumbents reporting growing share of rack-power revenue via integrator/ODM programs",
   "updates": "increases"
  },
  {
   "signal": "Rack-level pre-integration announcements (PDUs shipped pre-installed in integrated racks)",
   "where": "OCP summit talks and rack-integrator (system-build) press releases for CE deployments",
   "threshold": "Pre-integrated racks specified in ≥2 flagship CE builds",
   "updates": "increases"
  }
 ],
 "mitigations": [
  {
   "action": "Run the three CE operator/distributor interviews already named in the node's promotion path, structured specifically to split direct-branded vs ODM/white-label vs distributor volume",
   "type": "information",
   "voiNodeId": "cust.operator-large",
   "note": "Replaces the misused 30%-of-orders stat with a sourced channel split; also de-risks cust.oem and cust.distributor"
  },
  {
   "action": "Develop an OEM/private-label variant of the product line so ODM-routed large-operator volume becomes addressable rather than foreclosed",
   "type": "strategic",
   "voiNodeId": null,
   "note": "Converts the channel risk into a second route to market at lower margin"
  },
  {
   "action": "Sign a CE master distributor with existing operator framework agreements to cover the mid/enterprise slice while direct large-operator qualification runs",
   "type": "contractual",
   "voiNodeId": null,
   "note": "Hedges Year-1 revenue against a slow direct channel"
  }
 ],
 "evidenceStatus": "contested",
 "evidence": [
  {
   "title": "OEM Rack PDU Solutions: Smart Power Distribution Unit for Global Data Centers",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "GETEKnet",
   "date": "2025-09-10",
